@node wcschr
@section @code{wcschr}---wide-character string scanning operation
@strong{Synopsis}
@example
#include <wchar.h>
wchar_t *wcschr(const wchar_t *@var{s}, wchar_t @var{c});

@end example
@strong{Description}@*
The @code{wcschr} function locates the first occurrence of @var{c} in the
wide-character string pointed to by @var{s}. The value of @var{c} must be a
character representable as a type wchar_t and must be a wide-character
code corresponding to a valid character in the current locale.
The terminating null wide-character string.

@*
@strong{Returns}@*
Upon completion, @code{wcschr} returns a pointer to the wide-character
code, or a null pointer if the wide-character code is not found. 

@*
@strong{Portability}@*
@code{wcschr} is ISO/IEC 9899/AMD1:1995 (ISO C).

No supporting OS subroutines are required.

@*
